    1.0   Introduction


    The MBMGEMAP Galactic Empire Planet Database Extract Utility is designed
		to work in conjunction with MBMGEGRF to provide your users with a tool 
		to generate custom, personal starmaps of your current Galactic Empire 
		Game. 

		Each night in the nightly cleanup MBMGEMAP will process the whole 
		MBMGEPLT.DAT file (it only takes a minute or two). It extracts out a 
		couple key pieces of information on each sector, planet, and wormhole 
		and writes it to the encrypted MBMGEPLT.MAP file. This file can then
		be downloaded by your users to enable them to render graphic starmaps 
		of your current GE game.

		This greatly enhances the enjoyment of the game by allowing users to 
		visualize the game map they are playing on. Additionally, with the 
		registered version of MBMGEGRF your users can generate GIF or PCX
		images that they can print and edit to suit themselves.
		
    This document describes the procedures to install and operate this 
    software. Please read it carefully prior to installation.
    





