    4.0   Operations


    MBMGEMAP is a simple program to operate. If you forget the command line 
    options simply run the program with the "-?" switch as follows;

    MBMGEMAP -?

    This will display a complete list of the command line options available
    as follows;

    USAGE:

     MBMGEMAP [-options]


		    -nxxxxxxxx      8 Digit GE Registration #

				                This is your 8 digit Galactic Empire Activation code.
												If you have forgotten this code simply look in the
												MBMGEMSG.MSG file.



		Examples:

   		mbmgemap -n12345678




    4.0    Operations (cont.)

		A batch file GECLEAN.BAT has been provided as an example how to automate
		the nightly generation of the map file. This batch should be appended
		to the end of your existing BBSCLEAN.BAT (if you have one). If you don't
		already have a BBSCLEAN.BAT use this batch as a sample one.

		Note: You will also need to create a Library directory to hold the
		nightly map file so your users can download it. You will need to use
		the library options to manually log in the file the first time and then
		can simply copy the new version into the library each night. In the
		example GECLEAN.BAT file I chose GEMAPS as the library name. You may 
		choose any name you like by simply changing the copy command in the 
		BBSCLEAN.BAT you create (or update).

		Some sysops may choose to use the GALUTIL utility to update the library
		so that it accurately reflects the file date and file size. Please 
		refer to your MajorBBS operations manual for information on GALUTIL.





